Just some basic comments:
> #!/bin/bash
set -e
> DIR=$1
> 
> mkdir $DIR
> cd $DIR
[...]
General rule: _*Allways*_ use quotes for variable expansion.
Reason:
$ md foo\ bar
$ DIR=Foo\ bar
$ cd $DIR
bash: cd: foo: No such file or directory
